" class="mw-reference-text"><i id="mwA10">"Study the Vedas daily. Perform diligently the duties ("karmas") ordained by them"</i>, <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.sankaracharya.org/sadhana_panchakam.php" id="mwA14">Sadhana Panchakam</a> of Adi Shankara</span></li><li about="#cite_note-95" id="cite_note-95"><a href="./Adi_Shankara#cite_ref-95" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-95" class="mw-reference-text">Anantanand Rambachan, <i id="mwA18">The limits of scripture: Vivekananda's reinterpretation of the Vedas.</i> University of Hawaii Press, 1994, pp. 124–125: <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external autonumber" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=b9EJBQG3zqUC&amp;pg=PA124&amp;dq=brahma+as+opposed+to+brahman&amp;lr=#PPA124,M1" id="mwA2A"></a>.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-96" id="cite_note-96"><a href="./Adi_Shankara#cite_ref-96" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-96" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Adi_Shankara#CITEREFIsaeva1993" about="#mwt292" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"harvnb","href":"./Template:Harvnb"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"Isaeva"},"2":{"wt":"1993"},"pp":{"wt":"57–58"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA2E">Isaeva 1993</a><span about="#mwt292" id="mwA2I">, pp.</span><span typeof="mw:Entity" about="#mwt292" id="mwA2M"> </span><span about="#mwt292" id="mwA2Q">57–58</span>. Quote: "Shankara directly identifies this awakened atman with Brahman and the higher knowledge. And Brahman, reminds the Advaitist, is known only from the Upanishadic sayings".</span></li><li about="#cite_note-michaelcomans-97" id="cite_note-michaelcomans-97"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Adi_Shankara#cite_ref-michaelcomans_97-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Adi_Shankara#cite_ref-michaelcomans_97-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></